<h2 style="color:green">
You should also know how to ... 
</h2>
<br/><br/>
<a name="TOC-Make-Edits-to-Work-Items-Elsewhere"></a>
<h3>
Make Edits to Work Items Elsewhere Show Up on the Prioritizer
</h3>

<p>
At this time, the Prioritizer doesn't update automatically for any updates made to Work items while you're away from the Prioritizer. So if you have the Prioritizer open in your browser, and want it to include changes you made to a Work record open in another browser tab, please use the browser refresh function.
</p>

<a name="TOC-Remove-an-Item-from-the-Filter-Tile"></a>
<h3>
Remove an Item from the Filter Tile after You've Edited It Out
</h3>

<p>
When you have an open Filter tile, if you edit the filtered value of any records on the Prioritizer, they won't automatically remove themselves from the Filter tile. So if you have a tile filtering by theme "GUS - Trust," then use the Mass Edit tool to remove that theme from a record, it will not automatically disappear from your filter tile-- at this time, you'd need to close and re-open the Filter tile to remove it from the filtered view, or refresh via the browser (which will also clear your filter selection).
</p>

